      "content": "It's a common misconception, but even a small amount of grapefruit juice can interact with your medication. The amount is not the issue; it's the interaction that matters. Grapefruit juice can significantly affect the way your body processes certain drugs, potentially leading to harmful side effects. It's always best to err on the side of caution and avoid grapefruit when you're on medication. Your health is too important to take chances with. Always consult your doctor for personalized advice.",
